    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Providence R. I.</placeName>
                <date>April 12<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1857</date>
            </p>
            <p>Rev. and Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">The Jews in this city are<lb/> now quite a congregation, &amp; they
                contemplate<lb/> the erection of an edifice in which to worship<lb/> the God of
                their fathers. Their means, by no means<lb/> large, are inadequate to build such a
                temple<lb/> as their hearts would desire. Having heard<lb/> that the late
                    <persName>Judah Touro</persName> of <placeName>New Orleans</placeName> left<lb/>
                in trust certain friends to aid in the erection of<lb/> houses for religious worship
                in places where<lb/> the receivers <add>of our faith</add> are few in numbers &amp;
                not abundant<lb/> in means, we, as a committee appointed by<lb/> the congregation,
                have taken the liberty to inquire<lb/> of you if such be the fact. We know of no
                one<lb/> to whom such inquiry could be more properly<lb/> addressed than to one who
                was honored with<lb/> that good man's confidence and regard.<lb/> We are, Sir, with
                great consideration</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Yours very truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">A Worinsers</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">B Shuman</persName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Penn</placeName>
            </p>
